  "prompt": "Why do I have to tip the server?",
  "response": "Tipping is a complex cultural practice, but here are some key reasons:\n\n1. Low base wages\n- In many places, servers are paid below minimum wage\n- Tips make up a significant portion of their income\n- Their hourly wage often doesn't cover basic living expenses\n\n2. Service industry structure\n- Restaurants typically expect customers to supplement server wages through tips\n- Tips are considered part of their compensation package\n\n3. Incentive for good service\n- Tips motivate servers to provide attentive and quality service\n- Better service can lead to higher tips\n\n4. Economic necessity\n- Many servers rely on tips to make a living wage\n- Tips can represent a substantial part of their total earnings\n\n5. Social custom\n- In some countries like the US, tipping is a strong social expectation\n- Not tipping can be seen as rude or inconsiderate\n\nWhile tipping practices vary by country and culture, in places like the United States, it's generally considered a standard practice in restaurants and other service industries.\n\nIf you disagree with tipping, some argue the solution is to support businesses that pay fair wages rather than not tipping individual workers who depend on tips.",
